definition: many/much/often/a lot of/numerous/more/in excess/how (to what extent)/multi-/Taiwan pr. [duo2] when it means "how"

sentences.english: I like the footballer Emmanuel Adebayor and I like the Togolese team.
sentences.chinese: 我喜歡阿德巴約，我也喜歡多哥國家隊。

sentences.english: Switzerland beat Togo 2-0, while Ukraine trounced Saudi Arabia 4-0.
sentences.chinese: 瑞士2比0戰勝多哥，而烏克蘭則以4比0大敗沙特。

sentences.english: It grants most-favoured-nation (MFN) treatment as a minimum to all its trade partners.
sentences.chinese: 對她的貿易伙伴，多哥最起碼同意以最惠國待遇對待。

sentences.english: My life is in England now with Arsenal and with Togo.
sentences.chinese: 我的現在是英格蘭的阿森納和多哥隊。

sentences.english: But it appears the Togolese government has had the final say.
sentences.chinese: 但是多哥政府已經有了最終的解釋。

sentences.english: Some Togolese refugees share the fate of their Benine se brothers.
sentences.chinese: 一些多哥難民與他們的貝寧兄弟遭受同樣的命運。

sentences.english: I am a native of Lome in Togo.
sentences.chinese: 我在多哥是一個洛美的本地人。

sentences.english: China appreciates the Togolese government and parliament for resolutely pursuing the one-China policy.
sentences.chinese: 中方讚賞多哥政府和議會堅定奉行一箇中國政策。

sentences.english: After the first half of the game, South Korea pushed for an equalizer against Togo.
sentences.chinese: 經過上半埸的賽事後，南韓盡力追和多哥。

sentences.english: The Togolese football federation said the match had been organized without its knowledge.
sentences.chinese: 多哥足球聯盟表示，這次比賽的組織他們並不知情。

sentences.english: How many have heard of [Togo player] Emmanuel Adebayor?
sentences.chinese: 多少人聽說過多哥球員阿德巴約？

sentences.english: The 32-year-old footballer was part of Togo's team that participated at the 2006 World Cup held in Germany.
sentences.chinese: 昌蓋還曾代表多哥參加了2006年德國世界盃。

definition: Côte d'Ivoire or Ivory Coast in West Africa
